  i  oppose  the  bill  due  to some valid and genuine reasons the bill which appears to do away with  the child labour  up  to  the  age  of  18  has  two  caveats  which  would  have  the  effect  of legitimizing  child  labour  through  backdoor  and  increase  exploitation  of  children the bill allows for legalizing child labour allowing children to work in socalled family  enterprises  would  legalize  at  least  threefourth  of  child  work  which presently  is  unlawful  legalizing  children  in  audiovisual  entertainment  industry will  put  them  in  harmful  situation    this  law  under  section  18  criminalises  the parents which is not in the best interest of the child the shortened schedule omits many  occupations  which  have  devastating  effects  on  the  physical  and  mental health of the child   